      "writtenOn": "2017-12-01T19:28:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "That makes sense to me conceptually, although I had never heard that before, and haven\u0027t been able to find anything suggesting it to be the case. Can you provide some details and/or links? (My understanding has been that the important part is where we call setjmp, rather than where jmp_buf is allocated.)\n\nIf jmp_buf must be stack-allocated, Chromium\u0027s JPEGImageDecoder has the same bug, AFAICT. (Its jmp_buf lives inside a struct which lives inside the JPEGImageReader class, which is allocated by new.)\n\nLikewise, libpng seems to store its jmp_buf on its png_ptr. Sometimes its local to that object (which is allocated with malloc), and sometimes it is malloc\u0027ed itself. (Some places internally it is on the stack.)",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 9,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 9,
        "endChar": 38
      },
      "revId": "0ccd3ffbd45aa76217320d566a6ef92d04307099",
