      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-01T19:57:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ok, I think I misinterpreted \"should\" here (as \"must\"). You\u0027re saying that we\u0027re better off stack allocating it in this case? This seems to be the right way to do it.\n\nI\u0027d recommend rewriting this as:\n\n\"Always stack-allocate jmp_buf, and pop it at the end of a stack frame, so that longjmp never returns to a stack frame that has already exited.\"",
      "parentUuid": "bc827851_7377fa71",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 9,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 9,
        "endChar": 38
      },
      "revId": "0ccd3ffbd45aa76217320d566a6ef92d04307099",
