      "writtenOn": "2017-12-01T19:14:55Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "libjpeg doesn\u0027t call longjmp. It\u0027s a Skia specific implementation for the error callback. Nesting is for cases like this:\n\nvoid SkDoSomething() {\n    AutoPushJmpBuf jmp(mgr);\n    if (!setjmp(jmp)) {\n        abort(\"SkDoSomething failed\");\n    }\n    ...\n\n    SkDoSomethingMoreSpecific();\n\n    ....\n}\n\nvoid SkDoSomethingMoreSpecific() {\n    AutoPushJmpBuf jmp(mgr);\n    if (!setjmp(jmp)) {\n        abort(\"SkDoSomethingMoreSpecific failed\");\n    }\n    ...\n}",
      "parentUuid": "bd9088a2_326eb534",
      "revId": "0ccd3ffbd45aa76217320d566a6ef92d04307099",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a958e4af_018090c7",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkJpegPriv.h",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 50,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-01T19:28:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e libjpeg doesn\u0027t call longjmp. It\u0027s a Skia specific implementation for the error callback. Nesting is for cases like this:\n\nThis is technically true, although if Skia did not call longjmp, I believe libjpeg would call exit(). (I know libpng does something similar.) longjmp is the recommended way to respond to an error.\n\n\u003e \n\u003e void SkDoSomething() {\n\u003e     AutoPushJmpBuf jmp(mgr);\n\u003e     if (!setjmp(jmp)) {\n\u003e         abort(\"SkDoSomething failed\");\n\u003e     }\n\u003e     ...\n\u003e \n\u003e     SkDoSomethingMoreSpecific();\n\u003e \n\u003e     ....\n\u003e }\n\u003e \n\u003e void SkDoSomethingMoreSpecific() {\n\u003e     AutoPushJmpBuf jmp(mgr);\n\u003e     if (!setjmp(jmp)) {\n\u003e         abort(\"SkDoSomethingMoreSpecific failed\");\n\u003e     }\n\u003e     ...\n\u003e }\n\nIndeed. I don\u0027t know whether we ever get into that situation, but without looking over the code again, I believe it\u0027s possible.\n\nI had thought that after calling SkDoSomethingMoreSpecific we would need to call setjmp again. I just read http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/utility/program/setjmp, and it seems to state that just using the original jmp_buf is good enough, although I\u0027m not confident in my understanding of the prose there.",
      "parentUuid": "c584c851_5b67be73",
      "revId": "0ccd3ffbd45aa76217320d566a6ef92d04307099",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
